  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Product Designer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Responsibilities: </strong><br /></p><ul><li>Conceptualize, design and create products for families under the group</li><li>Design graphics and prints for merchandise and lifestyle product offerings</li><li>Sketching, producing technical drawings and tech packs</li><li>Sourcing and selecting of fabrics and materials</li><li>Seeing products through from initial illustrations to the creation of samples and finished products</li><li>Conceptualizing launch campaigns together with the marketing team.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong> <br /></p><ul><li>At least 2 years of working experience in fashion and/or product design, or a relevant field.</li><li>Proficient in Adobe Creative Suite, including Illustrator and Photoshop.</li><li>Experience in sketching/illustration, passionate about bringing product drawings to life.</li><li>Experience in sewing and working with textiles.</li><li>Experience in graphic design and photography are a bonus.</li><li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills.</li><li>Fashion forward and able to spot what resonates with consumers.</li><li>Ability to multitask, prioritize, and meet deadlines in a fast-paced environment.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
